In this modified code, we use `DATE_TRUNC('day', TO_TIMESTAMP("unixTime"))` to truncate the "unixTime" column to the date part only. Then, we compare it with `TO_DATE(@unixDate, 'YYYY-MM-DD')`, where `@unixDate` is the Unix timestamp for today's date (without the time component). Rows with the same date as today's date will be updated.

